The paper deals with self-assembly systems, which are a type of distributed system. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph rewriting and graph grammars, which are topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the topology of self-assembling systems, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the convex hull of the space inhabited by agents, which is a topic in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses complexity measures, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
